                </form>
            </div>
        </div>
    
        <div class="processing-section">
            <img src="./images/wool1.png" alt="Sorting Process" class="left">
            <div>
                <p>
                    The sorting process in wool production involves categorizing and organizing freshly sheared raw wool based on 
                    various characteristics such as fiber length, diameter, and color. This step is crucial for maximizing the value 
                    of the wool. Skilled workers carefully examine and separate the wool into different grades or lots, ensuring that 
                    fibers with similar attributes are grouped together. Sorting enhances the marketability of the wool, as it allows 
                    for the creation of higher-quality products and the fulfillment of specific customer demands. Proper sorting is an 
                    essential quality control measure that ensures the final wool products meet industry standards and expectations.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="btn-container">
                <form action="/sorting" method="post">
                    <button class="btn">Read me....</button>
                </form>
            </div>
        </div>
    
        <div class="processing-section">
            <p>
                The dyeing process in wool production is an optional step where raw wool is treated with dyes to add color. 
                It involves immersing the wool in dye solutions to achieve desired shades and patterns. Dyeing enhances the 
                versatility and market appeal of wool products by offering a broader range of colors and styles. This process 
                requires attention to detail, as factors like dye selection, temperature control, and immersion time impact the 
                final result. Dyeing can be a creative and value-adding step for wool farmers, allowing them to cater to diverse 
                customer preferences and increase the marketability of their products.
            </p>
